#StringBuilder
    • In java, StringBuilder class provides a mutable sequence of characters.
    • Used for append, insert new content in StringBuilder objects.
    • Unlike string which is immutable, StringBuilder allows modification of characters sequence without creating new objects
    • StringBuilder is not synchronized, thus it is used for single threaded application
    
    syntax:
    StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder("initialString");

    + StringBuilder class has three constructor:
        • StringBuilder() -> Construct an empty string builder with capacity 16
        • StringBuilder(capacity : int) -> Construct an empty string builder with specified capacity 
        • StringBuilder(s: string) -> Construct a string builder with specified string


    
#StringBuffer
    • StingBuffer class in java represent a sequence of characters that can be modified. It is also a mutable sequence of characters.
    • Used for append, insert new content in StringBuffer objects.
    • Unlike String, we can modify the content of a StringBuffer without creating a new objects.
    • All the method of StingBuffer are synchronized, making it safe to multithreaded environments.

    syntax:
        StingBuffer s = new StringBuffer();